  "body": "I am learning Truffle by using the [Conference](https://github.com/eshon/conference) example from Eva Shon.  \n\nChanging the Truffle build path for the app.js file in the top level truffle.js config appears to cause the resulting app.js in the build directory to be incomplete and then throw errors when used.\n\nUsing \n\n``` js\n\"app.js\": [ \"javascripts/app.js\", \"javascripts/hooked-web3-provider.min.js\"]\n```\n\nworks fine, but using\n\n``` js\n\"js/app.js\": [ \"javascripts/app.js\", \"javascripts/hooked-web3-provider.min.js\"]\n```\n\nresults in a much smaller file that is missing the bluebird capabilities. The messages in the console still say that the code has been compiled without issue.\n\n``` console\nUsing environment development.\nServing app on port 8080...\nRebuilding...\nCompleted without errors on Fri Jun 17 2016 10:54:35 GMT+0100 (BST)\n>> File truffle.js changed.\nRebuilding...\nCompleted without errors on Fri Jun 17 2016 11:05:23 GMT+0100 (BST)\n```\n\nThe stylesheets don't seem to be effected by changing their destination path.\n",
